John F. MAEDER et al., Appellants, v. JOHN R. THOMPSON CO., Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. May 25, 1926.) No. 3424. John M. Henry, of Pittsburgh, Pa., for appellants.

Before BUFFINGTON, WOOLLEY, and DAVIS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

After argument and due consideration had, the motion to dismiss is granted.
